name: CETARTIODACTYLA
wikitext: Cetartiodactyla is the Whippomorpha. Alternatively, the term 'Cetartiodactyla' is used to denote a clade where Cetacea evolved alongside Artiodactyla and not within it. Under this definition, all artiodactyls, including hippos, are more closely related to one another than any are to the whales.
